The paper proposes a framework for training deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The framework involves adjusting the weighting of examples, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. The manipulation of derivatives is a key aspect of the framework, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
